# Neuromorphic UI Standards (All Agents)

## Mandatory

1. **CSS variables** – Use `--neu-bg-primary`, `--neu-shadow-dark`, `--neu-shadow-light`, etc. from `neuromorphic-styles.css`. Never hardcode neuromorphic colors.

2. **Dark mode** – Apply `.neuromorphic-dark` class when `next-themes` reports dark mode. Use `NeuromorphicProvider` which handles this automatically.

3. **Component props** – Use size variants, states, and accessibility props consistently. All neuromorphic components support `className`, `aria-*` where applicable.

## Forbidden

- Hardcoded shadow/background colors on neuromorphic pages
- Non-neuromorphic shadows (e.g. `shadow-lg` from Tailwind) on neuromorphic components – use `.neu-raised`, `.neu-inset`, `.neu-flat` instead
- Skipping `NeuromorphicProvider` when building neuromorphic pages

## Component Standards

- **NeuButton:** Use `variant` (default, primary, success, etc.), `isLoading`, `fullWidth`
- **NeuCard:** Use `NeuCard`, `NeuCardHeader`, `NeuCardContent` for structure
- **NeuBadge:** Use `variant` for semantic colors
- **NeuTabs:** Use `tabs`, `activeIndex`, `onTabChange` with `NeuTabsContent` for panels

## Over-Video / Dark-Background Text (Critical)

When content sits over dark video or dark gradients (hero sections, device pages, apps portal):
1. Mark the section with `data-over-video` on the containing section or wrapper.
2. Text over dark backgrounds must stay white — do NOT follow light/dark theme for these elements.
3. Override classes in neuromorphic-styles.css: `.portal-hero-badge`, `.portal-hero-title`, `.device-hero-title`, `.device-cta-over-video`, etc.
4. Green accents: always `text-green-400`.
5. CTA buttons: light mode = dark text on light button; dark mode = white text.
6. Device pages: Mushroom1, SporeBase, Hyphae1, MycoNode, Alarm — wrap in NeuromorphicProvider, add data-over-video to video/dark hero sections.

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must have `neu-focus` for focus-visible outline
- Tooltips use `aria-describedby`
- Modals use focus trap and Escape to close
